```

## Key Takeaways

* Loops are used to repeat code.
* A for loop contains initialization, condition, and update.
* i++ increases a variable by 1.
* console.log(i) prints the value of the variable.
* console.log("i") prints the text "i".
* Loops reduce repetitive code and improve efficiency.
